A ship...?

217
00:31:52,028 --> 00:31:54,187
And nobody managed to go upstream?

218
00:31:57,659 --> 00:31:59,487
Do you want to see it for yourself?

219
00:31:59,829 --> 00:32:02,285
We can continue on foot, if you wish.

220
00:32:08,965 --> 00:32:10,293
What does it say?

221
00:32:10,842 --> 00:32:13,001
That we should remain silent.

222
00:32:13,095 --> 00:32:17,557
Whoever speaks will be swallowed by the evil spirits of the whirlwind.

223
00:32:53,393 --> 00:32:57,012
The Indians call whirlpools Chirimagua...

224
00:32:57,148 --> 00:32:59,188
"the choleric spirits".

225
00:32:59,859 --> 00:33:03,111
Whoever falls there is lost.

226
00:33:03,488 --> 00:33:05,898
They also say that...

227
00:33:05,992 --> 00:33:09,492
"Water has no hair to cling to."

228
00:33:37,530 --> 00:33:39,191
Is this a rubber tree?

229
00:33:41,702 --> 00:33:44,953
Yes. Brazilian rubber tree.

230
00:33:57,888 --> 00:34:03,049
They call it cauchuch, the weeping tree.

231
00:34:03,394 --> 00:34:06,229
These indigenous people love the flowery language.

232
00:34:06,523 --> 00:34:11,566
They call gold the sweat of the sun, and bees the mothers of honey.

233
00:34:14,074 --> 00:34:18,489
